                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1216 M/350.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 5, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Minister of Fomento has informed the Foreign Office that up to May
                    thirty-first no request for a new concession relating to the Imperial Valley
                    canal system had been received, and if any request for a new concession should
                    be presented the representations of the Embassy would be taken into
                    consideration. The Foreign Office adds that in December, 1907, the President
                    decided to defer granting any concession covering the waters of the Colorado
                    River until a satisfactory agreement about the distribution thereof had been
                    reached between the United States and Mexico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
